   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Before starting the work instruction activity, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Do not begin these tasks without confirmation that personnel directly
                     involved have completed the required training associated with the work
                     instruction activity and have reviewed this document.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Gather necessary tools and equipment as identified below in the Equipment
                     Section.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Wear and use additional Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and safety
                     equipment required for this specific work instruction.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Obey all applicable safety requirements and procedures.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Notify appropriate personnel of the activity and estimated time needed to
                     complete the tasks.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Clearly identify, mark-off, and secure the designated area defined by the
                     work instruction activity.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Follow all Lockout/Tagout procedures when work instruction activity requires
                     isolating energy in the designated area. Verify energy is isolated before
                     starting work.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>After verifying that energy is isolated, remove the protective guarding and
                     open the safety interlock gates.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Prerequisites</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Obtain a commercial quality container with a known height value measured and
                     approved by the quality team.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Monitor the production flow to ensure that the machine is properly set up in
                     accordance with Work Instruction INS-03-100 Container Handling Setup - Tiama -
                     MX4.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image1.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To set up the motor-driven movable frame, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Confirm the motor-driven movable frame height adjustment in accordance with
                     Work Instruction INS-03-100 Container Handling Setup - Tiama - MX4.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Jog a commercial quality container of the type to be inspected into station 5
                     or other station where FTA is installed on the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol>
                        <li>The MX4 should be in Manual mode <image href="media/image3.jpg" placement="inline"/>.</li>
                        <li>Move the container using the <image href="media/image4.jpg" placement="inline"/> selector.
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify that the gauge light is on.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol>
                        <li>The gauge signal is shown on the status bar. When the container can be
                           inspected, the gauge light changes from gray to green.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <title>Tiama MX4 Gauge Light:</title>
                        </fig>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For the mechanical setup of the FTA Head Assembly, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Select Detections &gt; FTA from the Main Menu.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select Settings &gt; Optics from the Main Menu.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig>
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Display the cross hairs on the finish surface image.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol>
                        <li>The MX4 should be in PAUSE mode <image href="media/image9.jpg" placement="inline"/> .</li>
                        <li>Activate the <uicontrol>Permanent</uicontrol> button <image href="media/image10.jpg" placement="inline"/> .</li>
                        <li>Press the <uicontrol>Cross</uicontrol> Hairs button to aid in setup
                              <image href="media/image11.jpg" placement="inline"/>.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_crx_kyd_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image12.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_drx_kyd_xcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the finish surface view and enable the laser.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_bq2_4yd_xcc">
                        <li>Activate the laser by clicking on the <image href="media/image13.jpg" id="image_q5s_4yd_xcc" placement="inline"/> button in the <i>FTA Laser Source
                                 Settings</i> menu.</li>
                        <li>The right image must show the finish surface with the cross hairs and
                           laser.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_qt2_wyd_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image14.jpg"
                                  id="image_rt2_wyd_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>If the container is not appearing on the screen, use the up/down and in/out
                     adjustments until an image appears.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_phm_5yd_xcc">
                        <li>Locking Handle (in/out) [1].</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (in/out) [2].</li>
                        <li>Locking Screw (up/down) [3].</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (up/down) [4]. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_p4q_xyd_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image15.jpg"
                                  id="image_q4q_xyd_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, slightly loosen the Locking Screws and
                     adjust the position of the Head Assembly left/right using the Adjustment Knob
                     until the sealing surface image is horizontal as in the image shown. When
                     finished, tighten the Locking Screws.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_rkx_1zd_xcc">
                        <li>Locking Screws (left/right) [1].</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (left/right) [2].</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_lln_bzd_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image16.jpg"
                                  id="image_mln_bzd_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, loosen the Locking Handle and adjust the
                     position of the Head Assembly in/out using the Adjustment Knob until the
                     sealing surface image is vertically centered as in the image shown. When
                     finished, adjust the Locking Handle.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_xlv_tzd_xcc">
                        <li>Locking Handle (in/out) [1].</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (in/out) [2].</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_lfv_vzd_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image17.jpg"
                                  id="image_mfv_vzd_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, slightly loosen the Locking Screw and
                     adjust the position of the Head Assembly up/down using the Adjustment Knob
                     until the vertical Wire Edge laser line is centered as in the image shown. When
                     finished, tighten the Locking Screw.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_cg4_d12_xcc">
                        <li>Locking Screw (up/down) [1].</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (up/down) [2].</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ant_f12_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image18.jpg"
                                  id="image_bnt_f12_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>When the laser is centered on the crosshairs, confirm that the sealing
                     surface of the container is in focus. If it is not, the FTA Head requires
                     realignment or repair.</p>
                  <p>
                     <note id="note_d5g_q12_xcc">
                        <p>The previous adjustment steps may need to be repeated until the image is
                           centered on the crosshairs. </p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_m3v_r12_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image19.jpg"
                                  id="image_n3v_r12_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Tilt adjustments (if installed).</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_jjr_v12_xcc">
                        <li>Tilt adjustment knob [1].</li>
                        <li>Tilt adjustment blocking screw [2].</li>
                        <li>Tilt adjustment default position pin [3]. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rnj_w12_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image20.jpg"
                                  id="image_snj_w12_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To adjust the FTA light and laser settings, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Sealing Surface Intensity slider until the Avg. Intensity
                     reads between 80 and 90. (Ideal intensity is 100).</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_iqc_cb2_xcc">
                        <li>The MX4 should be in Manual mode and the article should not
                              rotate.</li>
                        <li>If the Sealing Surface Intensity value must be adjusted to near 100 to
                           obtain the desired measured intensity, this may indicate that the FTA
                           Head needs servicing.  </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ykq_cb2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image21.jpg"
                                  id="image_zkq_cb2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_alq_cb2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image22.jpg"
                                  id="image_blq_cb2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Sealing Surface Balance slider to obtain an even contrast
                     throughout the image from top to bottom.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_hr2_pb2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image23.jpg"
                                  id="image_ir2_pb2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Laser Intensity.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_sky_zc2_xcc">
                        <li>Activate the laser by clicking on the <image href="media/image24.jpg" id="image_gxh_bd2_xcc" placement="inline"/> button in the <i>FTA Laser Source
                                 Settings</i> menu.</li>
                        <li>Move the Laser Intensity slider until the Avg. Spot Width slider
                           turns to green.</li>
                        <li>The ideal Avg. Spot Width is 4.0.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_bdy_2d2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image25.jpg"
                                  id="image_cdy_2d2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_aqm_fd2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image26.jpg"
                                  id="image_bqm_fd2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For the software setup of the FTA, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Spin the container:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_qhm_ld2_xcc">
                        <li>The machine should be in Manual mode [1].</li>
                        <li>Press the <uicontrol>Green</uicontrol> button [2].</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ldf_md2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image27.jpg"
                                  id="image_mdf_md2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select Settings &gt; FTA Defect Adjustment.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_qgx_td2_xcc">
                        <li>The MX4 should be in Pause mode <image href="media/image28.jpg" id="image_nh4_rd2_xcc" placement="inline"/>.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_oh4_rd2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image29.jpg"
                                  id="image_ph4_rd2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_qh4_rd2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image30.jpg"
                                  id="image_rh4_rd2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Click on the <image href="media/image31.jpg" id="image_jl1_yd2_xcc" placement="inline"/> button
                     to show the finish edges on the trapped image.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_s4m_yd2_xcc">
                        <li>Select the Sealing Surface image.</li>
                        <li>Select one of the 64 frames.</li>
                        <li>Verify the green top and blue bottom arcs match with the finish
                           edges.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ew5_b22_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image32.jpg"
                                  id="image_fw5_b22_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Learn the Top and Bottom finish limits.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ssk_222_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <image href="media/image33.jpg" id="image_nfd_f22_xcc" placement="inline"/>
                           button.</li>
                        <li>Drag the Top and Bottom blue lines to the Top and Bottom limits of the
                           Finish surface as shown.</li>
                        <li>Press the <uicontrol>Learn</uicontrol> button.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ydx_f22_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image34.jpg"
                                  id="image_zdx_f22_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the Article Type.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_cbk_l22_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <image href="media/image35.jpg" id="image_l31_m22_xcc" placement="inline"/>
                           button.</li>
                        <li>Choose the proper Article Type as needed.<ol id="ol_tng_422_xcc">
                              <li>Normal: Used for most containers. It should always be used for
                                 initial setup regardless of the actual bottle type.</li>
                              <li>Rough: Selected when finish edges are rough (due to a dirty
                                 finish) or blurred due to the curvature of a crown finish.</li>
                              <li>No Step: Basically used for Blow &amp; Blow process if Normal
                                 finish is not working (false rejects for Overpress or Wire Edge).
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                     <note type="note" id="note_xwm_p22_xcc">
                        <p>Changing the Article type will restore the parameters values back to
                           their defaults.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ywm_p22_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image36.jpg"
                                  id="image_zwm_p22_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the Image Contrast and Luminosity.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_cyt_y22_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <image href="media/image37.jpg" id="image_onz_y22_xcc" placement="inline"/>
                           button.</li>
                        <li>Move the Contrast and Luminosity sliders as required to better see the
                           surface image.</li>
                        <li>This affects the displayed image only. It does not change the optical or
                           light setup done previously.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_fjp_z22_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image38.jpg"
                                  id="image_gjp_z22_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Show the Over height/Under height values.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_pdm_2f2_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <image href="media/image39.jpg" id="image_n1f_ff2_xcc" placement="inline"/>
                           button.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Sealing Surface</uicontrol> button.</li>
                        <li>The bottom image will show a green dot graphic with the values measured
                           from the frames. The red lines are the threshold values defined. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_fqm_ff2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image40.jpg"
                                  id="image_gqm_ff2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Show the Wire Edge height values.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_cb2_sf2_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Wire Edge Height </uicontrol>button.</li>
                        <li>The bottom image will show a green dot graphic with the values measured
                           from the frames. The red line is the threshold value defined.</li>
                        <li>Negative values mean Overpress.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_yyf_tf2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image41.jpg"
                                  id="image_zyf_tf2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Set up the revolutions per gauge.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ikq_yf2_xcc">
                        <li>Select Settings/Advanced Parameters.</li>
                        <li>Confirm the Rev Per Gauge value is set to 1.50.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_zrv_zf2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image42.jpg"
                                  id="image_asv_zf2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To verify there is no stray light coming from nearby stations (NCI, NCL or others), perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Jog 3 containers into the machine:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_o3s_dg2_xcc">
                        <li>One (1) in the station after FTA.</li>
                        <li>One (1) in the FTA position.</li>
                        <li>One (1) in the station before FTA.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_fhz_fg2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image43.jpg"
                                  id="image_ghz_fg2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Spin the containers.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_rz2_mg2_xcc">
                        <li>The MX4 should be on MANU mode.</li>
                        <li>Press the <uicontrol>ON</uicontrol> button.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_b3v_mg2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image44.jpg"
                                  id="image_c3v_mg2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Trap the next 10 images.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rzx_pg2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image45.jpg"
                                  id="image_szx_pg2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Check for stray light on the Sealing Surface, Wire Edge and Crizzle
                     images.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>Possible solutions:</p>
                     <ol id="ol_uy3_xg2_xcc">
                        <li>Mask the NCL light source.</li>
                        <li>Change the position of the NCI lamp.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_cc5_zg2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image46.jpg"
                                  id="image_dc5_zg2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>If there is no possibility to reduce stray light on the left side of the
                     image by changing the position of the NCI lamp or masking the NCL lamp, set the
                     WE Offset Left Column to 0.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_wh2_2h2_xcc">
                        <li>Enter to Settings/Advanced Parameters.</li>
                        <li>Select the Left Column Offset parameter.</li>
                        <li>Modify the value to 0.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_yvz_fh2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image47.jpg"
                                  id="image_zvz_fh2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_xwl_gh2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image48.jpg"
                                  id="image_ywl_gh2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rpc_hh2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image49.jpg"
                                  id="image_spc_hh2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To review the Pockets screen of the FTA, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Select Settings &gt; Pockets from the Main Menu.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_dhy_lh2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image50.jpg"
                                  id="image_ehy_lh2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Clear out all the totals by pressing the<uicontrol> Reset Values</uicontrol>
                     button <image href="media/image51.jpg" id="image_jgl_ph2_xcc" placement="inline"/>.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ufw_rh2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image52.jpg"
                                  id="image_vfw_rh2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Start the machine (ensure production ware is available at the infeed).</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_hhc_t32_xcc">
                        <li>The numbers shown are the median values obtained during the 15 minute
                           inspection interval.</li>
                        <li>As the containers travel through the pockets, each number will turn
                           black or red when a sufficient number of containers have passed.</li>
                        <li>The numbers will be displayed in black when acceptable (&gt;80% of set
                           threshold), or red when below the 80% of the threshold. The FTA Head is
                           properly adjusted when all these numbers are black.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_anf_w32_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image53.jpg"
                                  id="image_bnf_w32_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Setting thresholds.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ops_1j2_xcc">
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Settings button </uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image54.jpg" id="image_l41_bj2_xcc" placement="inline"/> .</li>
                        <li>Select Alarm configuration <image href="media/image55.jpg" id="image_ocm_bj2_xcc" placement="inline"/> .</li>
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Threshold option </uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image56.jpg" id="image_znw_bj2_xcc" placement="inline"/> .</li>
                        <li>Set the threshold values.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_zjg_dj2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image57.jpg"
                                  id="image_akg_dj2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To confirm the FTA inspection and the appropriate inspection channels are
               enabled.</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Enable the FTA channels.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_sry_gj2_xcc">
                        <li>Select Settings &gt; Advanced adjustments.</li>
                        <li>Confirm the appropriate inspection channels are enabled (in orange)
                           according to the FTA section of MSDR INS-03-030 Minimum Inspection
                           Channels on Soul Equipment.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ezg_3j2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image58.jpg"
                                  id="image_fzg_3j2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the Reject Parameter settings are within the ranges specified in the
                     FTA section of MSDR INS-07-031 Inspection Device Setup Parameters for Soul
                     Equipment.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_kwt_jj2_xcc">
                        <li>Go to Settings &gt; FTA Defect Adjustment.</li>
                        <li>Select each Reject Parameter to modify the desired
                           settings/thresholds.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_yrr_wj2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image59.jpg"
                                  id="image_zrr_wj2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_tlx_1k2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image60.jpg"
                                  id="image_ulx_1k2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify that the FTA inspection is enabled.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_h41_hk2_xcc">
                        <li>The MX4 should be in Manual Mode.</li>
                        <li>Select Configuration<image href="media/image61.jpg" id="image_rrq_hk2_xcc" placement="inline"/>&gt; Detector
                              Presence<image href="media/image62.jpg" id="image_srq_hk2_xcc" placement="inline"/> to display the
                           Presence Detections display.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>station 5</uicontrol> (or the station where the
                           FTA is installed) button.</li>
                        <li>Click on the<uicontrol> FTA inspection </uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image63.jpg" id="image_szf_jk2_xcc" placement="inline"/> to display the FTA
                           verdict activation screen.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_g2c_kk2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image64.jpg"
                                  id="image_h2c_kk2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the FTA inspection IS NOT inhibited.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_mjn_mk2_xcc">
                        <li>Select Utilization &gt; Inhibition.</li>
                        <li>Confirm the FTA inspection IS NOT in orange. (Orange means the
                           inspection is inhibited.)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_cyb_qk2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image65.jpg"
                                  id="image_dyb_qk2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the defect mapping function in the MX4 software.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_nrr_sk2_xcc">
                        <li>Select Utilization<image href="media/image66.jpg" id="image_pr4_tk2_xcc" placement="inline"/> &gt; Rejects
                              Table<image href="media/image67.jpg" id="image_qr4_tk2_xcc" placement="inline"/> to display the
                           Rejects table screen.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <uicontrol>FTA Box</uicontrol>. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_r1f_yk2_xcc">
                           <image href="media/image68.jpg"
                                  id="image_s1f_yk2_xcc"
                                  placement="break"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Upon completion of tasks, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Replace protective guarding and close safety interlock gates.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Confirm the designated work area is clear and communicate to personnel the
                     intent to restart energy.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>After the designated work area is confirmed clear and personnel are aware of
                     the pending restart, follow all Lockout/Tagout procedures to restart energy
                     supplied to the designated area. Verify energy is active.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Remove signs and markings from the designated work area.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Perform basic housekeeping duties. Clean up the work space, tools and
                     equipment, dispose of trash, put tools and equipment in assigned area.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Notify appropriate personnel that the work instruction activity has been
                     completed.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
